#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code exact sum = goal wale subarrays ko directly count nahi karta,
balki formula use karta hai:

Exact(goal) = AtMost(goal) - AtMost(goal - 1)

1. helper(nums, goal) function count karta hai kitne subarrays ka sum at most goal hai.
2. Sliding window use hoti hai:
   - right se sum badhate hain
   - agar sum > goal ho jaaye, to left aage badha ke sum kam karte hain
3. Har step par current valid window se
   (right - left + 1) subarrays milte hain.
4. Fir:
   - val1 = at most goal
   - val2 = at most goal-1
   - inka difference = exactly goal

Main idea:
Binary array me sliding window se “at most sum” easily nikal sakte hain,
aur exact sum uske difference se mil jaata hai.

Important:
Agar goal < 0 ho jaaye, to answer 0 hoga,
isliye helper me us case ko handle kiya gaya hai.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {

    public int helper(int[] nums, int goal){
        if(goal < 0) return 0;
        int left = 0;
        int right = 0;
        int cnt = 0;
        int sum = 0;

        while(right < nums.length){
            sum += nums[right];

            while(sum > goal){
                sum -= nums[left];
                left++;
            }
            cnt += (right - left + 1);
            right++;
        }
        return cnt;
    }

    public int numSubarraysWithSum(int[] nums, int goal) {
        int val1 = helper(nums, goal);
        int val2 = helper(nums, goal-1);
        int result = val1 - val2;
        return result;
    }
}
